import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='income_per_capita')
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income_per_capita', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income per capita across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='income_per_capita', y='total', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income per capita and total population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['income_per_capita'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='income_per_capita', hue='group', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['income_per_capita'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['income_per_capita'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="region", y="total", data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of total population by region?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
